A quantitative index used to determine the relative importance of an indigenous plant species, which was calculated as follow:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$UVs = \Sigma Ui /n$$\end{document}UVs=ΣUi/n
where Ui is the sum of the total number of use citations by all informants for a given species, n is the total number of informants21. A high use value indicates the potential importance of the cited plant species.

This index shows the local importance of each species and it is given by the frequency of citation (FC, the number of informants mentioning the use of the species) divided by the total number of informants participating in the survey (N), without considering the use-categories as follow22:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${RFC}_{s}=\frac{{FC}_{s}}{N}=\frac{\sum_{i={i}_{1}}^{{i}_{N}}{UR}_{i}}{N}$$\end{document}RFCs=FCsN=∑i=i1iNURiN

This index was measured with multiplying three factors using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${CV}_{s}=\left[\frac{{NU}_{s}}{NC}\right]\times \left[\frac{{FC}_{s}}{N}\right]\times \left[\sum_{u={u}_{1}}^{{u}_{NC}}\sum_{i={i}_{1}}^{{i}_{N}}\frac{{UR}_{ui}}{N}\right]$$\end{document}CVs=NUsNC×FCsN×∑u=u1uNC∑i=i1iNURuiN
where in the first factor, NUs the number of different uses cited for the species and NC is the total number of use-categories. FCs is the relative frequency of citation of the species in the second factor. Finally, the third factor is the sum of number of participants who mentioned each use of the specie (URui) divided by N23.

This index was calculated using the following formula.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
